From Philip Moyer Subject Re text of White House announcement and Q As on clipper chip encryption In article Brad Templeton writes Let's assume for the moment that the system really is secure unless you get both halves of the encryption key from the two independent escrow Let's say you even trust the escrow houses one is the ACLU and the other is the And I'm not entirely joking about those two names In that case the Prince of Wales has nothing to worry about on this I must respectfully disagree with this assertion The government is notoriously sloppy with physical communications and information They can't keep their computers safe and they're trying Read DEA is Not Adequately Protecting National Security Information GAO IMTEC for an excellent example of what I'm talking Private sector organizations tend to be even more lax in their security I believe that the escrow organizations will be penetrated by foreign intelligence services within months if not weeks of their Private organizations that lack the resources of a full fleged intelligence service will take longer perhaps on the order of one to two Nonetheless the penetrations will take place without Philip Moyer ECN Software Staff Engineering Computer Network Voice Fax